---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About - Astro Photo Stream Demo">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8">About This Demo</h1>
      
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-8">
        This demo site showcases the capabilities of the <strong>astro-photostream</strong> integration, 
        demonstrating how easy it is to create professional photo galleries with Astro.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">What You're Seeing</h2>
      
      <ul class="space-y-3 mb-8">
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 bg-blue-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mr-3 mt-1">
            <span class="text-blue-600 text-sm">✓</span>
          </span>
          <span><strong>Zero-config setup</strong> - The photo gallery works out of the box with minimal configuration</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 bg-blue-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mr-3 mt-1">
            <span class="text-blue-600 text-sm">✓</span>
          </span>
          <span><strong>Responsive design</strong> - Galleries adapt perfectly to mobile, tablet, and desktop screens</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 bg-blue-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mr-3 mt-1">
            <span class="text-blue-600 text-sm">✓</span>
          </span>
          <span><strong>EXIF metadata extraction</strong> - Camera settings, GPS coordinates, and timestamps are automatically processed</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 bg-blue-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mr-3 mt-1">
            <span class="text-blue-600 text-sm">✓</span>
          </span>
          <span><strong>Tag-based navigation</strong> - Photos are automatically organized by tags for easy discovery</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 bg-blue-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mr-3 mt-1">
            <span class="text-blue-600 text-sm">✓</span>
          </span>
          <span><strong>SEO optimization</strong> - Dynamic OpenGraph images and structured data for better search visibility</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 bg-blue-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mr-3 mt-1">
            <span class="text-blue-600 text-sm">✓</span>
          </span>
          <span><strong>Performance optimized</strong> - Static generation, lazy loading, and image optimization</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">AI Features (When Enabled)</h2>
      
      <p class="mb-4">
        When AI metadata generation is enabled with an API key, the integration can:
      </p>
      
      <ul class="space-y-3 mb-8">
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 bg-green-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mr-3 mt-1">
            <span class="text-green-600 text-sm">AI</span>
          </span>
          <span>Generate compelling titles and descriptions automatically</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 bg-green-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mr-3 mt-1">
            <span class="text-green-600 text-sm">AI</span>
          </span>
          <span>Suggest relevant tags based on image content</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 bg-green-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mr-3 mt-1">
            <span class="text-green-600 text-sm">AI</span>
          </span>
          <span>Resolve GPS coordinates to readable location names</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 bg-green-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mr-3 mt-1">
            <span class="text-green-600 text-sm">AI</span>
          </span>
          <span>Maintain consistent voice and style across your photo collection</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Technical Implementation</h2>
      
      <p class="mb-4">
        This demo site uses:
      </p>
      
      <ul class="space-y-2 mb-8">
        <li><strong>Astro 5.x</strong> - The modern web framework for content-focused sites</li>
        <li><strong>Tailwind CSS</strong> - For rapid UI development and responsive design</li>
        <li><strong>Content Collections</strong> - Astro's type-safe content management system</li>
        <li><strong>Static Site Generation</strong> - Pre-rendered pages for optimal performance</li>
        <li><strong>TypeScript</strong> - Full type safety throughout the application</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Get Started</h2>
      
      <p class="mb-4">
        Ready to add a photo gallery to your Astro site? It's as simple as:
      </p>
      
      <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
        <pre class="text-green-400"><code>npx astro add astro-photostream</code></pre>
      </div>
      
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4">
        <a 
          href="https://github.com/walterra/astro-photostream" 
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="bg-gray-900 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold hover:bg-gray-800 transition-colors text-center"
        >
          View on GitHub
        </a>
        <a 
          href="https://github.com/walterra/astro-photostream#quick-start" 
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="border-2 border-gray-900 text-gray-900 px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold hover:bg-gray-900 hover:text-white transition-colors text-center"
        >
          Read Documentation
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>